COPYRIGHT RULES
- When changing the GPL header of any source file (thus removing the info that
  it comes from the Ghost project), you MUST include the above notice in the header.
- When using a larger part of the sources, include this file in the root
  directory of where the sources lie, as a file named "GHOST-COPYRIGHT"
  (or don't remove it in the first place).
- When using parts of the sources in any application, include the copyright notice
  in an appropriate location (for console applications, this should be the "--version"
  screen; for GUI applications, the credit screen, if there is one).
